---
/**
 * Creature submission license page.
 *
 * Linked from the submit form (A2). Explains in plain language what the
 * creator agrees to when they submit a creature. The LICENSE_VERSION export
 * is imported by the submit form and stored on every insert so we know which
 * version of the license was accepted at submission time.
 */
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

export const LICENSE_VERSION = 'v1-2026-04';
---

<Base
  title="Creature Submission License"
  description="What you agree to when you submit a creature to the Matlu creature encyclopedia."
>
  <h1>Creature Submission License</h1>
  <p class="version">Version {LICENSE_VERSION} &mdash; April 2026</p>

  <p class="lead">
    When you submit a creature to Matlu, you're sharing something you made.
    Here's what that means in plain language.
  </p>

  <section class="terms">
    <h2>What you're agreeing to</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>You created this.</strong> The creature, its name, its story, and any
        drawing or photo you upload were made by you (or by a child you are responsible for).
        You are not copying someone else's work.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>We can use it.</strong> By submitting, you give Fills Pills permission to
        display your creature on the Matlu wiki, include it in the game, and create pixel
        art based on your description. We will always credit you by the name you provide.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>You keep it too.</strong> You still own your creature. This license does
        not take it away from you — we're asking to share it, not buy it.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Credit stays with the creature.</strong> If your creature appears in the
        game, your name (or the creator name you enter) will appear in the credits.
        We will not remove the credit later.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>We may not use every submission.</strong> Submitting does not guarantee
        your creature will appear in the game. Creatures go through a review process.
        We may edit descriptions for length or clarity before publishing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>For creators under 18.</strong> A parent or guardian must give permission
        before submitting. By ticking the parental consent box on the form, the adult
        confirms they have read this license and agree on the child's behalf.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="questions">
    <h2>Questions?</h2>
    <p>
      If something here is unclear, or if you want to withdraw a submission, open an issue
      on the <a href="https://github.com/FilipMarzuki/matlu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Matlu GitHub repository</a>
      and we'll sort it out.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="back">
    <a href="/creatures/submit">&larr; Back to the submission form</a>
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .version {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent-hi);
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  li {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  li strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .questions p { max-width: 540px; }

  .back {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
